main event: Two unidentified flying objects were observed in Rolla, Missouri on 15-16 September 1965.
interesting points: The objects were noticed traveling toward the horizon over a period of 15 minutes., Witnesses described one of the objects as red and narrow, drifting slowly., An astronomer suggested that the objects could have been satellites or a high-flying plane., The description of the objects did not match any known satellites., The report mentions frequent sightings of unidentified objects in the area, as reported in newspapers.
witness description: two individuals, a husband and wife, observed the objects while driving
